description: The molecule is a guaiacyl lignin obtained by cyclodimerisation of coniferol. It has a role as a plant metabolite and an anti-inflammatory agent. It is a member of 1-benzofurans, a primary alcohol, a guaiacyl lignin and a member of guaiacols. It derives from a coniferol.
answer: The molecule is a guaiacyl lignin that is found in Arabidopsis thaliana and Anastatica hierochuntica. It has a role as a plant metabolite and is a member of 1-benzofurans, a primary alcohol, a guaiacyl lignin, a member of guaiacols, and a lignan. It is functionally related to a coniferol and a sinapyl alcohol.

description: The molecule is an unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 8,9-epoxy-(5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoic acid. It is a long-chain fatty acyl-CoA and an unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA. It derives from an 8,9-EET. It is a conjugate acid of an 8,9-epoxy-(5Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatrienoyl-CoA(4-).
answer: The molecule is a complex organic compound with multiple functional groups including alkenes, ethers, thioesters, amides, alcohols, phosphates, and nucleosides.

description: The molecule is an alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)]-D-GlcNAc where the glucosamine at the reducing end has beta-configuration at its anomeric centre. It has a role as an epitope.
answer: The molecule is Alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)]-beta-D-GlcpNAc is an alpha-L-Fucp-(1->2)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->4)]-D-GlcNAc where the glucosamine at the reducing end has beta-configuration at its anomeric centre; Lewis b. It has a role as an epitope.

description: The molecule is a Glu-Cys-Gly tripeptide derivative of glutathione containing a 2-hydroxyethyl substituent on the S of the Cys residue. It derives from a glutathione.
answer: The molecule is S-(2-hydroxyethyl)glutathione, a Glu-Cys-Gly tripeptide derivative of glutathione containing a 2-hydroxyethyl substituent on the S of the Cys residue. It is functionally related to a glutathione.

description: The molecule is a pyrrolopyrimidine that is 7-methyl-7H-pyrrolo[2,3-d]pyrimidin-4-amine which has been substituted at position 5 by a 4-fluoro-2,3-dihydro-1H-indol-5-yl group, the nitrogen of which has been acylated by a (6-methylpyridin-2-yl)acetyl group. An orally bioavailable PERK inhibitor. It has a role as an EC 3.1.3.48 (protein-tyrosine-phosphatase) inhibitor, a PERK inhibitor and an antineoplastic agent. It is a pyrrolopyrimidine, a biaryl, a member of indoles, a member of methylpyridines, an organofluorine compound and a tertiary carboxamide.
answer: The molecule is GSK2656157 is a pyrrolopyrimidine compound that acts as a PERK inhibitor, among other roles.
